"{\"uid\": \"news4sanantonio.com-news-local-from-marshall-high-school-to-team-usa-keith-sandersons-journey-to-the-2024-olympics\", \"text\": \"Now  44\\u00b0  Wed  65\\u00b0  Thu  54\\u00b0  President Donald Trump holds his 9th cabinet meeting at the White House.  byMatt Roy  SAN ANTONIO - This weekend when you are tuning in for the 2024 Olympics, keep an special eye on the Team USA Shooting.  San Antonio kidKeith Sandersonis repping the squad in the 25M rapid fire pistol competition.  From Marshall High School to Team USA: Keith Sanderson's journey to the 2024 Olympics  For the 49-year-old Marshall high school graduate, fourth time might be the charm.  \\\"I was born in Massachusetts, but we moved down to San Antonio, I remember, on the last day of first grade,\\\" Sanderson said. \\\"Which is why I have a mixture between really liking lobster and New England seafood and Tex-mex and Mexican food. Taco Cabana. I am always talking about Taco Cabana.\\\"  Sanderson will be competing in the Olympics and representing Team USA for the fourth time this year. His first was back at the 2008 Beijing games, where heentered the final round with the lead, but ended up finishing fifth.  {sd-embed class=\\\"sd-embedded-media\\\" data-alt=\\\"FINALS%20-3.jpg\\\" data-caption=\\\"Photo%20by%7B%7DJoshua%20Schave/USA%20Shooting\\\" data-duration=\\\"\\\" data-externalid=\\\"c1682a95-ea33-430c-b643-94f4872677b0\\\" data-mediatype=\\\"image\\\" data-renditions=\\\"%7B%22large16x9%22:%7B%22blurSigma%22:-1,%22height%22:3255,%22label%22:%22large16x9%22,%22scaleWidth%22:986,%22url%22:%22/resources/media2/16x9/5784/986/0x598/90/c1682a95-ea33-430c-b643-94f4872677b0-FINALS3.jpg%22,%22width%22:5784,%22x%22:0,%22y%22:598,%22uuid%22:null,%22id%22:%22b3876afc-0967-46fe-92ea-5d522f67d48e%22,%22preciseWidth%22:null,%22preciseHeight%22:null,%22name%22:%22large16x9Url%22,%22rendition%22:%22large16x9%22,%22labelOrConvertedName%22:%22large16x9%22%7D,%22jumbo16x9%22:%7B%22blurSigma%22:-1,%22height%22:3255,%22label%22:%22jumbo16x9%22,%22scaleWidth%22:1320,%22url%22:%22/resources/media2/16x9/5784/1320/0x598/90/c1682a95-ea33-430c-b643-94f4872677b0-FINALS3.jpg%22,%22width%22:5784,%22x%22:0,%22y%22:598,%22uuid%22:null,%22id%22:%222660f7e0-7cb0-40b8-96cf-915420559919%22,%22preciseWidth%22:null,%22preciseHeight%22:null,%22name%22:%22jumbo16x9Url%22,%22rendition%22:%22jumbo16x9%22,%22labelOrConvertedName%22:%22jumbo16x9%22%7D,%22small16x9%22:%7B%22blurSigma%22:-1,%22height%22:3255,%22label%22:%22small16x9%22,%22scaleWidth%22:160,%22url%22:%22/resources/media2/16x9/5784/160/0x598/90/c1682a95-ea33-430c-b643-94f4872677b0-FINALS3.jpg%22,%22width%22:5784,%22x%22:0,%22y%22:598,%22uuid%22:null,%22id%22:%22239d40d5-0a4c-494c-b655-c4e4eb17f21d%22,%22preciseWidth%22:null,%22preciseHeight%22:null,%22name%22:%22small16x9Url%22,%22rendition%22:%22small16x9%22,%22labelOrConvertedName%22:%22small16x9%22%7D,%22full16x9%22:%7B%22blurSigma%22:-1,%22height%22:3255,%22label%22:%22full16x9%22,%22scaleWidth%22:5784,%22url%22:%22/resources/media2/16x9/5784/5784/0x598/90/c1682a95-ea33-430c-b643-94f4872677b0-FINALS3.jpg%22,%22width%22:5784,%22x%22:0,%22y%22:598,%22uuid%22:null,%22id%22:%22f7469203-a0a3-46fe-a1c7-cddb848eb5ec%22,%22preciseWidth%22:null,%22preciseHeight%22:null,%22name%22:%22full16x9Url%22,%22rendition%22:%22full16x9%22,%22labelOrConvertedName%22:%22full16x9%22%7D,%22medium16x9%22:%7B%22blurSigma%22:-1,%22height%22:3255,%22label%22:%22medium16x9%22,%22scaleWidth%22:648,%22url%22:%22/resources/media2/16x9/5784/648/0x598/90/c1682a95-ea33-430c-b643-94f4872677b0-FINALS3.jpg%22,%22width%22:5784,%22x%22:0,%22y%22:598,%22uuid%22:null,%22id%22:%2233930db7-d644-4865-b460-49d811167428%22,%22preciseWidth%22:null,%22preciseHeight%22:null,%22name%22:%22medium16x9Url%22,%22rendition%22:%22medium16x9%22,%22labelOrConvertedName%22:%22medium16x9%22%7D%7D\\\" data-thumburl=\\\"/resources/media2/16x9/5784/648/0x598/90/c1682a95-ea33-430c-b643-94f4872677b0-FINALS3.jpg\\\" data-title=\\\"Keith%20Sanderson,%20four-time%20Olympian%20from%20San%20Antonio%20\\\" data-url=\\\"\\\" data-defaultthumb=\\\"true\\\" data-embed-file=\\\"%0A%20%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class=%22sda-ImageEmbed%22%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cimg%20src=%22/resources/media2/16x9/5784/648/0x598/90/c1682a95-ea33-430c-b643-94f4872677b0-FINALS3.jpg%22%20alt=%22%22%20/%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%3Cdiv%20class=%22sda-ImageEmbed-caption%22%3EPhoto%20byJoshua%20Schave/USA%20Shooting%3C/div%3E%0A%20%20%20%20%3C/div%3E\\\" data-embed-type=\\\"image\\\" contenteditable=\\\"false\\\"}{/sd-embed}  He also competed in 2012 in London and 2016 in Rio.  Sanderson says the competition keeps him coming back.  \\\"Well, I have never done any drugs - well, anything more powerful than Benadryl or Aspirin, but I imagine that it's like heroin or crack or something, it's an addiction,\\\" he said.  After graduating from Marshall, Sanderson joined the Marine Corps where he joined their shooting team. That is where he discovered and fell in love with the sport of shooting.  \\\"I am never going to beat Michael Phelps in the pool,\\\" he said. \\\"I just do not have that genetic set of things that you need. But shooting was weird because I was able to see from the very beginning in the Marine Corps that this is different than running or lifting weights or doing something else. This is something where everyone is on an equal footing.\\\"  For years he got better and better and then in 2008 he got invited to the Olympics for the first time.  Photo by Brittany Nelson/USA Shooting  \\\"My most memorable experience was when I walked in to compete on my first day of competition, when I walked onto the field of play. When I did it for the Olympics representing America, it was a different world.\\\"  Sanderson hit his peak in the years after those Olympics, eventually becoming number one in the world in the late ought's, but injuries, miscues, and a string of bad luck kept him from performing to his standards in the 2012 and 2016 games.  He says he has been improving day by day and thinks he is primed for a good showing in Paris.  He also says he has some simple advice for young aspiring Olympians.  \\\"Each day just suck less,\\\" he said semi-jokingly. \\\"You do not have to be perfect, you just have to get better.\\\"  If you want to catch Sanderson and the rest of Team USA at the Olympics, he is competing in the 25 meter rapid fire pistol events.  Pre-event training is on Saturday.  Stages one and two are on Sunday and the final, should he make it, is on Monday.  Catch all the action on News 4 San Antonio.  2025Sinclair, Inc.\"}"